text:
ICICI Bank announced its financial performance for Q4 FY25 recently.

Here are the key highlights:

Financial Performance for Q4 FY25
· Core operating profit grew by 13.7% Y-o-Y to ₹17,425 crore
· Profit after tax grew by 18.0% Y-o-Y to ₹12,630 crore
· Net interest income (NIl) rises by 11.0% Y-o-Y to ₹21,193 crore
· Average deposits grew by 11.4% Y-o-Y to ₹14,86,635 crore

Financial Performance for FY 2025
· Core operating profit grew by 12.5% Y-o-Y ₹65,396 crore
· Profit after tax grew by 15.5% Y-o-Y to ₹47,227 crore
· Total period-end deposits grew by 14.0% Y-o-Y to ₹16,10,348 crore at March 31, 2025
· Added 241 branches during Q4-2025. The Bank had a network of 6,983 branches and 16,285 ATMs & cash recycling machines at March 31, 2025.

Further, the Bank’s Board has recommended a dividend of ₹11 per share for FY2025. The declaration and payment of dividend is subject to requisite approvals.

Read more - https://t.co/9grd6eaH0b

We extend our gratitude to all for continued patronage of our banking services. #InServiceOfTheNation #DeshKiSevaMeinICICI
